@EndNode

@Node "Note"

    Pointers to deallocate the local environment in the library base is saved
    in the fields pr_ExitCode and pr_ExitData of the Process structure of
    the macro. At exit a chain of pr_ExitCode(pr_ExitData) is called.
    Details are avaible on request.

    Some funtions are avaible only if a peculiar stack is running or installed:
    - Miami functions are avaible only if Miami is runnning;
    - Miami packets filter functions are avaible only if a registered
      version of Miami is running;
    - Genesis functions are avaible only if Genesis is installed;
    - user group functions are avaible only if the stack running offers
      the usergroup.library .

    When a function is not avaible, the user is informed via a requester
    and an ARexx error 15 (function not found) is returned.

    Miami-registered-only functions returns error if used with Miami not
    regitered.

    rxsocket.library/IsLibOn can be used to test the environment.
@EndNode
